# Environment Variables Template
# Generated: 2025-01-09
# 
# IMPORTANT: Replace all placeholder values with your actual Supabase project credentials
# Never commit real API keys to version control

# =============================================================================
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================

# Your Supabase project URL
# Format: https://[PROJECT_REF].supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co

# Your Supabase project ID (same as PROJECT_REF)
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=YOUR_PROJECT_REF

# Supabase Anonymous Key (safe to expose in frontend)
# This key has limited permissions based on your RLS policies
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=YOUR_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================

# Node environment (for development/production builds)
NODE_ENV=production

# Base URL for your application (if different from default)
# VITE_BASE_URL=https://yourdomain.com

# Analytics or third-party service keys (if used)
# VITE_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID=GA-XXXXXXXXX
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=https://your-sentry-dsn

# =============================================================================
# FINDING YOUR SUPABASE CREDENTIALS
# =============================================================================

# 1. Go to your Supabase project dashboard
# 2. Navigate to Settings > API
# 3. Copy the following values:
#    - Project URL → VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#    - Project API keys → anon/public key → VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
#    - Project reference ID → VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================

# - The anon key is safe to expose in your frontend code
# - Never expose your service_role key in frontend applications
# - Use environment variables in production deployments
# - Add .env to your .gitignore file
# - Consider using different projects for development/staging/production

# =============================================================================
# VERIFICATION
# =============================================================================

# After setting up your environment variables:
# 1. Restart your development server
# 2. Check browser console for connection errors
# 3. Test authentication functionality
# 4. Verify data loading from your database
# 5. Test file uploads to storage buckets

# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT PLATFORMS
# =============================================================================

# For Vercel:
# Add these variables in your Vercel project settings

# For Netlify:
# Add these variables in your Netlify site settings

# For custom hosting:
# Ensure your build process includes these environment variables